  "prompt": "Do anti-money laundering regulations exist?",
  "response": "Yes, anti-money laundering (AML) regulations exist in many countries and at international levels. These regulations are designed to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income. Key examples include:\n\n1. United States:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n\n2. International:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- European Union's Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n\n3. Typical requirements include:\n- Customer identification\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious activities\n- Maintaining financial records\n- Implementing compliance programs\n\nThese regulations apply to financial institutions, banks, cryptocurrency exchanges, and other businesses that handle financial transactions.",
